From: Dan Premachuk <DanPremachuk@CUNET.CARLETON.CA>
Sent: Wednesday, August 28, 2024 7:34 PM
Cc: Tony Bailetti <TonyBailetti@cunet.carleton.ca>; Kelly Phelan <KellyPhel=
an@cunet.carleton.ca>
Subject: Kick off your "TIM Journey" and the Fall term with an exciting nig=
ht with TIM faculty and staff at the ballpark!


Sent on behalf of TIM Academic Director, Tony Bailetti



Dear new TIM students, hello.



Welcome to the TIM community! We are very excited to have you join the TIM =
program, and we=92ve planned something special just for YOU. Join us for FR=
EE at a thrilling evening under the lights at the Ottawa Stadium, cheering =
on the Ottawa Titans while meeting your fellow TIM students and getting a s=
neak peek at the groundbreaking TIM projects launching this Fall.



This night is about YOU, our new TIM students and their loved ones, more th=
an it is about the ballgame! Here=92s why you won=92t want to miss it:

  *   Official TIM Welcome: Be warmly welcomed into the TIM Program as a fi=
rst-term student by the TIM Director, TIM faculty, TIM staff and TIM studen=
ts in their 4th term who are working on their TIM projects
  *   Build Connections: Network with your peers who are also gearing up fo=
r an incredible program.
  *   Exclusive Sneak Peek: Get an insider=92s view of the innovative TIM p=
rojects that will be making waves this season.

Game Details:

  *   Date: Thursday, August 29th
  *   Time: 6:30 PM
  *   Location: Ottawa Stadium, 300 Coventry Road
  *   Opponent: New York Bulldogs

To reserve your FREE spot, simply reach out to Dan Premachuk, our TIM Progr=
am Administrator, at dan.premachuk@carleton.ca<mailto:dan.premachuk@carleto=
n.ca>. Bring your loved ones with you.



This is more than just a game=97it=92s the perfect way to kick off your TIM=
 journey, make new friends, and immerse yourself in the TIM spirit from day=
 one. So grab your ticket, bring your energy, and let=92s create some unfor=
gettable memories together at the ballpark!



We can=92t wait to see you there!



Warm regards,

Tony Bailetti, Ph.D.
Academic Director, TIM Program
Sprott School of Business

Carleton University



